ed_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"score\": 0.8581582794952675, \"rank\": 0.03896103896103429, \"text\": \"Olympic Trials\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's all-around winner at trials automatically makes the Olympic team.\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 365, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's all-around winner at trials makes the team if he is also among the top three on three of the six apparatuses.\", \"from\": 366, \"to\": 485, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"2024 Xfinity U.S.\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 504, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 492, \"end\": 499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\", \"score\": 0.845867291513711, \"rank\": 0.11850642245707416, \"text\": \"Xfinity\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gymnastics Championships Live Broadcast Schedule  NBC and CNBC broadcasts also stream on NBCSports.com and the NBC Sports app.\", \"from\": 505, \"to\": 631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 555, \"end\": 558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999816970209121, \"rank\": 9.327950314777172e-06, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 563, \"end\": 567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"score\": 0.9974337057291067, \"rank\": 0.002572895546194465, \"text\": \"CNBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\"}, {\"begin\": 594, \"end\": 607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCSports.com\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 616, \"end\": 626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999556339277141, \"rank\": 4.431542878881933e-05, \"text\": \"NBC Sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Selection committees will choose the rest of the team members, taking into account results at nationals and trials as well as past meets in this Olympic cycle.\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 792, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's field is headlined by Olympic all-around gold medalists Simone Biles and Suni Lee.\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 862, \"end\": 874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}, {\"begin\": 879, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Suni Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles made her 2024 competition debut by winning the Core Hydration Classic on May 18 to stay undefeated in the all-around since returning last summer from a post-Tokyo Olympic break.\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 1073, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She improved on her world-leading all-around score in this Olympic cycle,according to the Gymternet.\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1174, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lee competed on three of four events at Classic and posted the top score on balance beam to boost her chances of making the Paris team.\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1311, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1176, \"end\": 1179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9999665015670139, \"rank\": 3.132263722222518e-05, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 1300, \"end\": 1305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999327567388, \"rank\": 6.724329749037024e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is working her way back after being diagnosed with two kidney diseases in early 2023.\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1401, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gabby Douglas, the 2012 Olympic all-around champion,withdrew from the meet on Wednesday due to an ankle injury, ending her Paris Olympic bid.\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1544, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1403, \"end\": 1416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabby_Douglas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabby Douglas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabby_Douglas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabby_Douglas\"}, {\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999327567388, \"rank\": 6.724329749037024e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shilese Jones, a two-time world all-around medalist, took second to Biles at Classic and has consistently been the top U.S. gymnast other than Biles over the last 20 months.\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1719, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1546, \"end\": 1559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shilese_Jones\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shilese Jones\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shilese_Jones\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shilese_Jones\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tokyo Olympic medalists Jordan Chiles and Jade Carey are also in contention to return to the Games after placing third and fourth in the all-around at Classic.\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1880, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1721, \"end\": 1726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999236263753125, \"rank\": 7.637911095841979e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1763, \"end\": 1773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Carey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jade Carey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Carey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Carey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the men's side, the U.S. Championships will include world all-around bronze medalist Frederick Richard, 2023 U.S. all-around champion Asher Hong and 2021 and 2022 U.S. all-around champion Brody Malone.\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 2086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1970, \"end\": 1979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_the_Great\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.171561242417093e-14, \"text\": \"Frederick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_the_Great\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_the_Great\"}, {\"begin\": 2019, \"end\": 2029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asher_Hong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\":